Akinwumi Adesina, president of the African Development Bank (AfDB), has congratulated Atiku Abubakar, former Vice-President for obtaining a master’s degree at the Anglia Ruskin University, Cambridge, United Kingdom. The former vice-president obtained a master’s degree in international relations. The AfDB president sent his congratulatory message via a tweet on Saturday. Adesina said the investment and devotion to higher education of the 2019 presidential candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) is “inspiring”. “I congratulate H.E. Atiku Abubakar @atiku former Vice President of Nigeria on passing 2 days ago his Masters in International Relations degree program at Anglia Ruskin University, Cambridge, UK,” Adesina said. “Your investments in & devotion to higher education are inspiring. Well done Sir!” I congratulate H.E. Atiku Abubakar @atiku former Vice President of Nigeria on passing 2 days ago his Masters in International Relations degree program at Anglia Ruskin University, Cambridge, UK. Your investments in & devotion to higher education are inspiring. Well done Sir! pic.twitter.com/9v9yn2K5sV — Akinwumi A. Adesina (@akin_adesina) November 13, 2021  In July, Adesina said the former vice-president contributed immensely to his emergence as head of the continental finance institution. This accomplishment will add to Abubakar’s educational curriculum vitae. In 1967, the former vice-president obtained a diploma from the School of Hygiene, Kano. He later obtained a law diploma at the Ahmadu Bello University with a regional scholarship in 1969. After obtaining the law diploma, he was absorbed into the Nigerian Customs Service.